From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [Q3.6-6] Unwrap OpenAI tool-definition envelope to inner function spec

Targets: templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja (state after Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 + Q3.6-4 + Q3.6-5 applied)

Harnesses speaking the OpenAI tool protocol send tool *definitions* wrapped
in an envelope: `{"type": "function", "function": {"name": ..., "parameters":
...}}`. Qwen3.6's upstream `<tools>` loop emits the whole wrapper via
`tool | tojson`, so the model sees an extra `type`/`function` layer it has to
peel off mentally, and the envelope keys cost tokens on every tool.

Fix: before serializing each tool, unwrap the envelope to its inner function
spec when the full envelope shape is present:

    {%- if tool is mapping and tool.type is defined and tool.type == 'function' and tool.function is mapping %}
        {%- set tool = tool.function %}
    {%- endif %}

Shape-strict on purpose. The guard requires `type == "function"`, a mapping
`function` member, AND an inner `name` — not merely `tool.function is defined`.
The inner-`name` requirement was added 2026-07-22 after review observed that a
tool carrying meaningful OUTER `name`/`description` alongside an unrelated
mapping `function` was unwrapped down to that member, silently discarding the
outer fields. A real OpenAI envelope always names its function, so requiring it
costs nothing; anything else now renders whole — noisy but lossless, which is
the safer failure for a malformed declaration. A tool that
happens to carry an unrelated top-level key named `function` (or a tool that
isn't a mapping at all) does NOT match the envelope shape and is emitted
unchanged. This is stricter than:

  - the gist this patch derives from (jscott3201 gist
    e4b155885cc68c038d6ac8909a3bd9fe, patch "Q5"), which guards only on
    `tool.function is defined` behind an `unwrap_tool_envelope` kwarg; and
  - the looser `tool_call.function is defined` unwrap this same template
    already does at the tool-CALL site (lines 110-112 upstream).

We intentionally dropped the gist's `unwrap_tool_envelope` kwarg escape hatch:
with a shape-strict guard the change is a no-op for anything that is not an
actual OpenAI envelope, so a per-request opt-out is unnecessary. (See
adversarial review note in docs/PATCH-CATALOG.md § Q3.6-6.)

Prior art: the unwrap convention is canonical in Qwen's own newer coder
template (Qwen/Qwen3-Coder-Next/chat_template.jinja, `tool.function` unwrap).
Independently surfaced for Qwen3.6 by the jscott3201 gist, snapshotted at
docs/sources/gists/jscott3201-e4b15588-qwen36-custom.jinja.

Stacks on Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 + Q3.6-4 + Q3.6-5. Diff is against the
Q3.6-5-applied state.

--- a/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
+++ b/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
@@ -76,6 +76,10 @@
     {{- "# Tools\n\nYou have access to the following functions:\n\n<tools>" }}
     {%- for tool in tools %}
         {{- "\n" }}
+        {#- Q3.6-6: unwrap the OpenAI tool-definition envelope ({"type":"function","function":{...}}) to the inner function spec. Shape-strict — requires type=="function" AND a mapping `function` — so a tool that merely carries a top-level `function` key (or is not a mapping) is left untouched. Analogous to the looser unwrap this template does at the tool-CALL site. -#}
+        {%- if tool is mapping and tool.type is defined and tool.type == 'function' and tool.function is mapping and tool.function.name is defined %}
+            {%- set tool = tool.function %}
+        {%- endif %}
         {{- tool | tojson }}
     {%- endfor %}
     {{- "\n</tools>" }}
